Token : 
Token is the smallest unit of information
They are the building blocks of code. 

Types of Token : 
1. Keywords 
Keywords are reserved words, whose meaning is already defined. We cannot use keywords as a variable names. There are 35 keywords in python.
Ex : if, else, for, while, def etc

2. Identifiers
User defined names
constant = uppercase
variable = lowercase
function = camel case 
class = pascal case

Note : 
Camel case = addProduct, addProductCategory
Pascal case = Hello, Demo 
Snake case = add_product, add_product_category 
Habib case = add-product, add-product-category 
Upper case = capital letters
Lower case = small letters 

3. Literals | constant
PI = 3.14
MAX = 100 

4. Separators (Punctuators) 
() = parenthesis
{} = curly brackets 
[] = square brackets 
, = comma 
: = colon 
; = semi-colon 
. = dot

5. Operators 
Operators are the symbols, which are used to perform some operations on one or more than one operand(variable and constant).

6. Datatype
Datatype simply represents the type of data. 

7. Variable 
Variable is the name given to memory location whose value may change during the execution of program.
Variable is going to be create when ever we sets value in it.

