full_name = "andrew Anderson"

Python variable have some naming rules : 

Rule 1 : Allowed characters
         Letters : a-z, A-Z 
         Digits : 0-9 
         Special Symbol : _ (underscore)

Rule 2 : Cannot starts with a digit 
         1name = "Gaurav"         invalid
         name1 = "Gaurav"         valid 

Rule 3 : No Special characters are allowed except underscore
         full*name = "Gaurav Kothari"     invalid 
         full_name = "Gaurav Kothari"     valid 

Rule 4 : Cannot use python keywords 
         class = 100           invalid 
         class_value = 100     valid 

Rule 5 : Case Sensitive 
         name = "Gaurav"   
         Name = "Kothari" 

Rule 6 : Meaningfull name
         total_marks = 375
         student_name = "John"

Rule 7 : Use Snake case (Python convention)
        first_name = "Gaurav Kothari"

    